[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":166},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002F2021\u002F04\u002F11\u002Fpip-command-not-found-fix\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002F2021\u002F04\u002F11\u002Fpip-command-not-found-fix\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002F2021\u002F04\u002F11\u002Fpip-command-not-found-fix\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002F2021\u002F04\u002F11\u002Fpip-command-not-found-fix\u002F":142,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002F2021\u002F04\u002F11\u002Fpip-command-not-found-fix\u002F":151},"\u002Fpython\u002F20210411\u002F4001503397\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":126,"date":127,"description":128,"extension":129,"lang":130,"meta":131,"navigation":132,"path":133,"readingMinutes":134,"seo":135,"standalone":136,"stem":137,"tags":138,"tldr":139,"updated":127,"url":140,"__hash__":141},"content\u002Fen\u002FPython\u002Fpip-command-not-found-fix.md","`command not found: pip` or `pip3` — Quick Fix","6998933404",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":120},"minimark",[11,16,29,31,40,44,47,60,71,94,99,103,116],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19,20,24,25,28],"p",{},"Was working on some Python stuff and tried to install packages, but ",[21,22,23],"code",{},"pip"," threw ",[21,26,27],{},"command not found: pip or pip3",". Quick note on the fix.",[12,30,23],{"id":23},[17,32,33,35,36,39],{},[21,34,23],{}," is a package manager for Python — similar concept to npm for Node.js. You install packages with ",[21,37,38],{},"pip install",".",[12,41,43],{"id":42},"command-not-found-pip","command not found: pip",[17,45,46],{},"This usually shows up if you've customised your terminal. Mine's themed, and every new command needs PATH tweaking.",[17,48,49,50,53,54,56,57,39],{},"First, try ",[21,51,52],{},"pip -V"," to see if there's a version number. If not, I'd suggest reinstalling Python. Per the official docs, ",[21,55,23],{}," is Python 2 — if you're on Python 3, use ",[21,58,59],{},"pip3",[17,61,62,63,66,67,70],{},"Then update your ",[21,64,65],{},".bash_profile"," and ",[21,68,69],{},".zshrc",":",[72,73,78],"pre",{"className":74,"code":75,"language":76,"meta":77,"style":77},"language-cmd shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","PATH=\"\u002FLibrary\u002FFrameworks\u002FPython.framework\u002FVersions\u002F3.5\u002Fbin:${PATH}\"\nexport PATH\n","cmd","",[21,79,80,88],{"__ignoreMap":77},[81,82,85],"span",{"class":83,"line":84},"line",1,[81,86,87],{},"PATH=\"\u002FLibrary\u002FFrameworks\u002FPython.framework\u002FVersions\u002F3.5\u002Fbin:${PATH}\"\n",[81,89,91],{"class":83,"line":90},2,[81,92,93],{},"export PATH\n",[17,95,96,98],{},[21,97,59],{}," should now work.",[12,100,102],{"id":101},"references","References",[104,105,106],"ul",{},[107,108,109],"li",{},[110,111,115],"a",{"href":112,"rel":113},"https:\u002F\u002Fstackoverflow.com\u002Fquestions\u002F42870537\u002Fzsh-command-cannot-found-pip",[114],"nofollow","zsh command cannot found pip",[117,118,119],"style",{},"html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}",{"title":77,"searchDepth":90,"depth":90,"links":121},[122,123,124,125],{"id":14,"depth":90,"text":15},{"id":23,"depth":90,"text":23},{"id":42,"depth":90,"text":43},{"id":101,"depth":90,"text":102},"Python","2021-04-11 21:49:37","Was working on some Python stuff and tried to install packages, but `pip` threw `command not found: pip or pip3`. Here's the fix.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002Fpip-command-not-found-fix","1",{"title":6,"description":128},false,"en\u002FPython\u002Fpip-command-not-found-fix",[23,126],null,"\u002Fen\